The European Union changes the rules for obtaining the visa
People must go to the Visa Applicant Service Centres before interviewing them in the Consular Section; the cost of waiting will be reduced.
As of 10 January 2011, the procedure for the treatment of visas at the United States Embassy and consulates will change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants will have to present themselves to the Visa Applicant Service Centres (ASC) before their interview in the Consular Section.
The ASC staff will receive the applicant's biometric information, which will be revised by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will bring certain benefits to the applicants, including the following:
The total cost of handling the visa will be lower, no longer will it be necessary to make a payment to obtain a date, another payment for the treatment of the visa and another for the mail service to deliver the document.
The vacuum cleaner will make a unique payment that will cover all three services.
The current rate will remain the same: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 in the case of visas on request (including visas for temporary workers) and $390 for commercial and investor visas.
Persons wishing to renew their visas should not present themselves for an interview with the Consular Representative, they will only present themselves at the nearest ESC where they will present the documents and will be given their fingerprints.
Because biometric information will be taken into the ASC, applicants wishing for a second meeting to be interviewed in the Consular Section will remain less time than before.
Similarly, visa applicants at the Consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the extra $26 service fee.
For further information on the new procedure for requesting visa, please visit http://mexico.usebassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
